intro: Amyema urdanetensis, commonly known as the Urdanet sedge, is a flowering plant belonging to the family Cyperaceae. It is native to South America, specifically found in Venezuela and Colombia. The plant is characterized by its grass-like appearance, with narrow, linear leaves and small, clustered flowers. It typically grows in moist, shaded environments such as forests and wetlands. Amyema urdanetensis is of interest to botanists due to its limited distribution and unique ecological adaptations.
